rComments: If you see this man as the prof... run. Didn't even teach, used an old profs lectures, was rude when asked questions, the assignments were horribly graded with such a specific marking rubric that you could not get right. Avoid avoid avoid avoid

Screw this guy. Literally used another profs lectures to teach the class which I'm pretty sure is plagiarism but what do I know. Grading is so inconsistent and there is no rubric for any of the assignments or tests so it is impossible to know exactly what the prof wants for each question. Avoid this man at all costs.

Course content was super interesting, however prof made the class unbearable. Prof didn't even teach his own lectures, and grading was super unfair. Don't take this class with this prof, it will ruin your GPA.

Vague and often erroneous evaluation questions with highly specific marking criteria that sets students up for failure. Is not open to feedback. Do not take classes with this professor if you value your time, money, and GPA.
Don't take this course with Pamenter. It is going to ruin your GPA. Very hard to do well due to the highly specific marking schemes that do not accurately test applications of your knowledge.

Obviously does not care about his students' success. Vague questions with an incredibly specific marking scheme. Made me hate the class and the material even though I normally find this type of content incredibly interesting. I don't think that this man should be a professor.

Broad evaluation questions but highly specific marking scheme that sets students up for failure. Doesn’t even teach, just posts pre-recorded lectures from an entirely different prof - I could have learned this material for free on youtube without hurting my bank account and gpa
Do not take a class with him, he does not even teach and use other's professor's lectures. Very arrogant. I regret taking the course with him.

Avoid this professor!!!!!!! He doesn't provide a positive learning environment for students, arrogant, doesn't teach, provides no accommodations, suspects academic fraud when you study hard and do well because he himself knows he made the marking scheme nearly impossible to achieve a good mark with. He absolutely hates to see students do well.

Stay away from Dr. Pamenter. General questions with extremely specific grading criteria, contesting will get you nowhere. You could legitimately say the exact same thing as the rubric but lose a point because he expects you to write the same way as him. Did not actually teach, this is not an exaggeration.

Great class and great attitude of prof. Arms open and leg down off a table the whole time during his office hour. He tends to book his office hour 10-20mins after the appointment with some awesome excuses. The course itself is hard but he has no marking criteria. He marks everything with his flow. The most helpful and kind prof
Very arrogant

Finally getting around to rating this prof. I think disappointing is the best description. University should make better choices and not force students to be tought by disinterested and arrogant profs.

This is a good course to actually meet and interact with the professor as the class is small and he and the TA spend the whole period walking around and helping student groups. The experiments can be frustrating and are not for the faint of heart!
Easy course if you put in the effort. We had a great class group and good discussions.
DA BOMB

He taught the very first part of the lecture, which honestly felt like he wasn't very familiar with the materials. He is kinda disorganized and the suggested reading had almost nothing to do with his lecture. Overall do not recommend it. It feels like the good comments about him (Below) are some fake comments written by him or his colleagues.

I don't love this course but it's a requirement for my program. Having to take it online is challenging. Still, the prof was helpful and probably the fastest responder to questions and emails that I've seen. That helped a lot.

Such a cool course! I never realized how hard it is do experiments with living animals but Dr. Pamenter was very helpful and the TAs were so caring. I definitely learned a lot and would recommend again.
Tough course but very interesting material. Online learning sucks but Dr. Pamenter was very accessible via email when I had questions and always provided helpful feedback quickly.

I was very nervous going into this course as I'm quite shy about public speaking but Dr. Pamenter was very encouraging and fostered a very welcome and comfortable classroom environment. He was also very accessible outside of the classroom and helped me a lot with my project.

I love this course! The content was very useful and I enjoyed the hands on experience. Dr. Pamenter was super approachable and easy to talk to! He answered all of our questions and was always happy to take the time to explain things or help with our experiments. I would definitely recommend!

Pamenter taught the first six lectures of BIO3350. Each lecture consisted of him attempting to read a pre-written script for each slide verbatim, culminating in a finished product that was ultimately just an error-riddled version of text-to-speech. Lectures often presented information that conflicted with what was presented in suggested readings.

Awful class and awful attitude of prof. Arms crossed and leg raised on a table the whole time during his office hour. He tends to cancel his office hour 10-20mins before the appointment with some weird excuses. The course itself isn't hard but he has no marking criteria. He marks everything with his flow. The most condescending prof
Super unclear when trying to get help. Horrible
I had no idea what he actually wanted throughout the term. The most unclear criteria and marking scheme ever.
THE WORST.
very condescending and ignorant. If this course is not mandatory, then do not take it. He is too arrogant for assistant prof.
just avoid. don't like this guy

I really like Matt! He is one of my favourite professor's at the university. He's super chill and easy to talk to. Experiments in Animal Physiology is one of the best courses I've had. I learned a lot and it was relatively easy to get a good grade if you put in the work. Dr. Pamenter makes it clear on his expectations. He is truly a stand up guy!!

He is the worst instructor I have ever encountered in my whole university year. He is rude, never clear on what he wants and most importantly cancel appointments 30mins before the meeting. He doesn't think our time is valuable. You can't just cancel appointments 4times a week. I am just sick of this guy. He doesn't deserve this position.
